<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Soviet-Golf,0122</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ground Broken For First Soviet Golf Course</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The first golf course is being built in the Soviet
Union.
   As a group of Swedish diplomats and area residents looked on
Saturday, a bulldozer began work on the course near the Swedish
Embassy in Moscow.
   The project is a joint venture of the Moscow Sport Committee and
a group of Swedish companies and will be finished in the fall, the
news agency Tass said.
   The course apparently will be off limits initially to most
Soviets, to whom the sport is alien. Tass said embassy workers and
foreign businessmen in Moscow will use the course and that a golf
school will be built for Moscow children.
</TEXT>
