<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Spain-Cocaine,0152</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Spanish Police Seize 1,235 Pounds Of Cocaine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BARCELONA, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police confiscated 1,235 pounds of
cocaine and arrested two people, including a U.S. citizen, an
official said.
   The cocaine was found in 19 bags on a beach near Barcelona, and
police suspect it was dropped there on Saturday by a ship sighted
off the coast earlier in the day, said Barcelona civil governor
Ferrand Cardenal.
   Reginaldo Blaco, a Cuban-born U.S. citizen, and Maria Arrarate
of Spain were arrested in connection with the confiscation,
Cardenal said on Sunday.
   No charges were immediately filed against them, and authorities
did not release an address in the United States for Blaco.
   Cardenal said the cocaine _ found in Vilanova Y Geltru, 30 miles
south of Barcelona _ represented one of the largest amounts of the
drug ever seized in Europe. He did not estimate the cocaine's
street value.
</TEXT>
