<HEAD>All Government Workers To Undergo Drug Tests In Malaysia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The nation's 870,000 government
workers will be forced to undergo urine tests for drug abuse, an
official said today.
   Yusof Noor, a government minister, told reporters that people
applying for 185,000 vacant government positions also will be
tested.
   There are an estimated 500,000 drug addicts in Malaysia out of a
population of 16.5 million. Officials said they did not believe
drug addiction is common among government workers and that the
testing was merely a precaution.
