<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--FastKingdom     04-25 0160</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Fast Kingdom,0166</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Church Built In Two Days</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GRAND HAVEN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Jehovah's Witnesses congregation met
in the church built in two days by about 650 people.
   Volunteers and congregation members from across Michigan began
work Friday on the 4,600-square-foot Kingdom Hall in Grand Haven
Township. It was near completion Sunday afternoon, said Phil Newell
of West Olive, a member of the congregation's building committee.
   ``We had our first meeting at 2 o'clock, and we're just
finishing up the landscaping work, spreading a little bark
around,'' Newell said. ``Everything came off beautiful. The
(township) inspectors were very impressed with the project and
excited to be part of it.''
   About a third of the 650 Jehovah's Witnesses who worked on the
project were skilled tradesmen who performed carpentry, plumbing
and electrical work, he said.
   Site and foundation work was done ahead of time.
   The new Kingdom Hall will seat 237 people, and cost the
congregation $170,000 to build.
</TEXT>
