<1ST_LINE>r a PM-People-Goetz     04-25 0224</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Goetz,0231</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Goetz Gives `Thanks' _ To Teens He Shot</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Subway gunman Bernhard Goetz received an award
from a gun club federation, then sarcastically ``thanked'' the four
young men he shot in December 1984 for helping him through his
legal battles.
   In a rare public appearance, Goetz on Sunday thanked each of the
four by name for foibles that he felt helped him to be acquitted on
attempted murder and assault charges.
   Goetz was convicted last year of lesser gun possession charges.
He is free on bail pending an appeal.
   In remarks before the Federation of New York State Rifle and
Pistol Clubs, Goetz thanked Barry Allen ``for robbing someone in
the apartment building where he lived.''
   He thanked Darrell Cabey ``for his revealing interview with
(columnist) Jimmy Breslin'' in which Cabey recounted the subway
shooting.
   Goetz thanked Troy Canty for his sometimes inconsistent
testimony and thanked James Ramseur ``for committing a tacky rape
and kidnapping'' and for his surly and uncooperative behavior in
the courtroom.
   The award the gun club gave Goetz goes annually to someone who
uses deadly force ``when reasonably necessary,'' according to
federation President Jerry Preiser.
   Preiser said the federation, which previously raised $10,000 for
Goetz's legal defense fund, raised $3,000 more for him Sunday and
hopes to raise $7,000 to $10,000 from mail solicitations.
</TEXT>
