<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Baby-Train,0176</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Train Kills Baby</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MULBERRY GROVE, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 17-month-old boy was hit by a
train as he crawled on railroad tracks near his home, authorities
said.
   Jeremy Lee Gerard, son of Ronald L. and Pamela Gerard of this
rural south-central Illinois community, was pronounced dead at the
scene Sunday, said Fayette County Coroner Angie May-Bolin.
   State police said the baby was hit as he crawled toward a
westbound Conrail mail train that was traveling about 70 mph. The
train, with three engines and 35 cars, was en route from
Plainfield, Ind., to St. Louis, state police said.
   Engineer Thomas B. Bridgegroom, 47, of Danville, Ind.,
apparently applied the brakes when he saw the baby, said Deputy
Coroner Jesse Miller.
   State's Attorney Don Sheafor refused to say much about the case
other than, ``It appears the child was outside unsupervised.''
   He said he did not know why the child was near the tracks, which
are south of the family home.
   The death remained under investigation, he said.
</TEXT>
