<2ND_LINE>AM-Milwaukee Fire, 2nd Ld - Writethru, a0484,0188</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Milwaukee Fire Leaves Three Injured</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout with all the missing now accounted for;
three injured in fire. No pickup.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By JOHN SOLOMON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MILWAUKEE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An explosion and fire ripped through a paint
store late Sunday and spread to four other buildings, injuring
three people, authorities said.
   The fire broke out at 11:15 p.m. and continued burning out of
control more than two hours later. Four buildings were engulfed in
flames when all off-duty firefighters were called in to staff
stations.
   After the explosion in the paint store, the blaze spread to
apartments upstairs, and to a tavern and brewery housed in a
converted bowling alley on the city's east side, fire officials
said.
   The building with the paint store was destroyed.
   Eight of the 12 people who lived in the building were initially
unaccounted for early Monday, said Dr. Jeffrey Jentzen, Milwaukee
County Medical Examiner.
   Later, police Lt. Donald Domagaleski said all were accounted for.
   The three injured were taken to a hospital, police said. No
information on their conditions was immediately available.
</TEXT>
