<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--Walkathon     04-25 0131</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Walkathon,0134</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Marchers Raise Estimated $42 Million For March of Dimes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An estimated $42 million was raised for the
March of Dimes by more than 600,000 Americans to fight birth
defects.
   Walkers in more than 1,300 communities marched an average of
15.5 to 18.6 miles in ``walkathons'' on Saturday or Sunday,
according to Marcia Stein, a spokeswoman for the organization.
   The walkers solicited pledges from friends, neighbors and
colleagues, who promised to pay them for each mile walked. The
money will be used to combat birth defects nationwide through
research, education and health services, Ms. Stein said.
   Pledges were up 5 percent over 1987. ``All indications are that
this year's walk will set a new record,'' March of Dimes President
Charles Massey said in a statement.
