Serra Club, sted Sierra Club.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Martin J. O'Dea</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Martin J. O'Dea, who climbed from a job as
office messenger to president of the Hibernia Bank, died Friday
after a long illness. He was 76.
   O'Dea, who began his banking career in 1928, was named
vice-president and manager of Hibernia's downtown San Francisco
branch in 1956. In 1963 he was elected director and in 1968 was
named president. He was past president of the Serra Club of San
Francisco.
