younger than us picked up on the drugs and forgot most of the rest
of what we were saying. Drugs were our biggest mistake.'' _ Ann
Hunter, at a reunion of 1960s Columbia University activists.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``Just a nice, neighborhood restaurant. A good bottle of wine, a
nice plate of pasta _ I mean, that's life.'' _ Elaine Kaufman, on
why Elaine's, her Italian restaurant in New York, has remained
popular among stars and stargazers for 25 years.
