<2ND_LINE>PM-Triple Murder, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0593,0334</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Three Found Slain `Execution-Style'
^Eds: SUBS 2nd-3rd grafs, `Lt. J.C. ..., with 2 grafs to UPDATE
with IDs. Contents of next-to-last graf may be offensive to some
readers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BASSETT, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The partially clad bodies of three people
were found by a motorist outside an abandoned pool hall, and
authorities said today the victims were killed execution-style by a
half-dozen shotgun blasts.
   The victims were identified as Bernie Gene McKnight, 30, of
Canton, Mich., and Paul H. Blackwood II, 26, and Lisa Rose Vega,
33, both of Osceola, said Lt. J.C. Brewer of the Mississippi County
Sheriff's Department.
   Brewer said the Osceola residents were apparently acquainted,
but he didn't know their connection, if any, to McKnight.
   Asked about a motive for the slayings, which apparently happened
Sunday night, Brewer said: ``We have got only speculation. We have
no suspects.'' He said his agency and state police investigators
were checking on possibilities that the deaths stemmed from a
domestic dispute or might have been drug-related.
   The bodies were discovered by a motorist in eastern Arkansas
about five miles from Interstate 55 and some 30 miles north of
Memphis, Tenn., said Mississippi County Sheriff Howard Carney.
   ``This area is out in the rural part of our county, off a gravel
county road. It's completely isolated,'' Brewer said.
   The bodies were about 10 feet apart, Carney said, and a
half-dozen spent 12-gauge shotgun shells were found on the ground.
   A 1988 Lincoln found at the scene was registered to the mother
of the Osceola man, Brewer said.
   Large portions of the victims' heads were blown away, officers
said, and two of the bodies also had extensive damage to their
arms, indicating they had placed their hands in front of their
faces as they were killed.
   According to Carney, one of the men had his shirt off and his
pants unzipped. The other man had his pants around his ankles. The
woman was clad only in sweatpants.
</TEXT>
