<HEAD>Richards Named Farm Editor of Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rick Richards of the Gary, Ind., Post-Tribune
on Monday night was announced as winner of this year's Glenn
Cunningham Farm Editor of the Year award by the Newspaper Farm
Editors of America.
   Richards and other annual contest winners were honored at the
association's 35th annual dinner at the National Press Club.
   Winners in specific categories included: farm news, Steve
Painter, The Wichita (Kan.) Eagle-Beacon; farm column, Painter;
farm feature, Dan Miller, Iowa Farmer Today, Cedar Rapids; and farm
series, Richards.
   Galen Moses of the Gainesville (Fla.) Sun was elected president
of the association, succeeding Sonja Hillgren, United Press
International, Washington, D.C.
   The association also voted to change the name to National
Association of Agricultural Journalists and to expand its
membership base to include agricultural magazine writers and
editors.
   Other officers include: Kathleen Davis, Lubbock (Texas)
Avalanche Journal, first vice president; and Audrey Mackiewicz,
Huron, Ohio, executive secretary-treasurer.
   Regional vice presidents named were:
   Northeast _ Roger Runningen, Small Newspapers, Washington, D.C.,
bureau.
   Southeast _ Thornton Hartley, Florida Times-Union, Gainesville
bureau.
   Midwest _ Kelly Boldan, Agri-News, Rochester, Minn.
   Southwest _ Steve Painter, The Wichita (Kan.) Eagle-Beacon.
   West _ Helen Willard, Prosser (Wash.) Record-Bulletin.
</TEXT>
