<1ST_LINE>r a BC-Montand     04-25 0304</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Montand,0317</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Yves Montand Honored by Film Society</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: No PMs Planned</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By MARY CAMPBELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Raquel Welch called Yves Montand ``a
spectacular film personality'' as the Film Society of Lincoln
Center paid tribute Monday night to the French actor.
   ``For Americans, especially American women, he is France,'' Miss
Welch said during the ceremonies in Avery Fisher Hall. ``He's a
spectacular film personality and about the most seductive singer in
the world.''
   Director Louis Malle called Montand ``one of the most romantic
figures the French cinema has ever known,'' adding: ``He represents
something unique in the French cultural world. Throughout his life
as a performer he has worked hard to avoid cliche.''
   Other speakers included Claude Berri, who directed Montand in
his two most recent films, ``Jean de Florette'' and ``Manon of the
Spring,'' and Costa-Gavras, Montand's director in ``Z,'' ``The
Confession,'' ``State of Siege,'' ``Clair de Femme'' and ``The
Sleeping Car Murders.''
   Mayor Edward I. Koch said of Montand, ``He's a superb film
actor, concert artist and, had he wanted to, could have been the
president of France.''
   Montand is the 17th recipient of a Film Society of Lincoln
Center tribute, the first from France. Charles Chaplin received the
first tribute in 1972, followed by Fred Astaire and Alfred
Hitchcock. Last year's honoree was Sir Alec Guinness.
   Montand said he remembered himself at 11, working in a factory
outside Marseilles, then using money he earned to see American
movies with subtitles.
   ``The 66-year-old boy is here tonight having a tribute. If you
can imagine what is going on here (pointing to his heart), you
understand that words are too weak and too futile.''
   The gala evening, which concluded with a dinner at the Tavern on
the Green, benefitted the society's fall New York Film Festival.
</TEXT>
