takeover offer from rival bidders whose joint buyout proposal
includes splitting the textile giant's assets among them.
   A special committee of Stevens' board informed fabric maker West
Point-Pepperell Inc. and the investment firm Odyssey Partners their
joint $68.50-a-share cash proposal was unacceptable in its present
form, Stevens said Friday.
</TEXT>
