<TEXT>
   Financier Carl C. Icahn has offered to buy the
23 percent of Trans World Airlines Inc. stock that he does not
already own, resurrecting his proposal to take the company private.
   Icahn, who is TWA's chairman, dropped a similar proposal after
the stock market crashed on Oct. 19.
   Under the plan announced Friday, stockholders other than Icahn
would receive for each of their shares a combination of $20 in cash
and $29 in face amount of notes paying 12 percent interest due in
2008.
</TEXT>
