they have agreed to acquire the cable systems of the former Storer
Communications for about $1.55 billion.
   The planned buyout announced Sunday by Comcast Corp. and
Tele-Communications Inc. comes months after a larger consortium
that included the two companies dropped a proposal to pay about
$2.9 billion for SCI Holdings.
   SCI was created when Storer was taken private by the investment
firm Kohlberg, Kravis & Roberts in a $2.5 billion leveraged buyout
in 1985.
