<TEXT>
   The United Auto Workers said
Chrysler Corp.'s decision to import the Dodge Aries and Plymouth
Reliant from Mexico next year threatens chances of an early
contract settlement and increases the likelihood of a strike.
   ``I hereby warn the Chrysler Corp. that if they cause these
negotiations to go in the ditch, the chances of a strike in
September would be 95 percent or better,'' UAW Vice President Marc
Stepp told a news conference Friday.
