<HEAD>London Shares Mixed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices were mixed Monday at midday on the
London Stock Exchange in a trendless market, with no significant
news to guide trading.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was up 2.4
points, or 0.1 percent, at 1,774.0 at about 12:30 p.m. local time.
   Volume was a modest 160 million shares, down sharply from 271.2
million shares at the same time on Friday.
   Major institutions again were largely absent from the market,
with many institutional clients only prepared to resume buying on a
large scale when the 100-share index falls to around the
1,750-point level, dealers said.
</TEXT>
