<1ST_LINE>r f BC-USWest     04-25 0167</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-U S West,0171</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Three Bell Companies Changing Name To U S WEST Communications</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   U S West Inc. said Monday that its three telephone
companies _ Mountain Bell, Northwestern Bell and Pacific Northwest
Bell _ will begin doing business later this year as U S West
Communications.
   U S West President Dick McCormick said the familiar bell symbol
will be retained and appear with the U S West Communications name.
He said the new name will be introduced over the next several
months and appear on bills and customer correspondence beginning in
July.
   ``The new name and market emphasis recognizes that many
customers, especially our multi-state customers, are dealing with
one company,'' McCormick said. He said the three telephone units
already are operating across company and state lines in 14 states.
   `We'll continue to use the names Mountain Bell, Pacific
Northwest Bell and Northwestern Bell for legal and regulatory
purposes, but we'll also being doing business as U S West
Communications,'' said McCormick.
</TEXT>
