<HEAD>TLC Group Mulls Sale of Three Beatrice International Companies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The investment firm TLC Group L.P. said Monday
it has retained Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. to explore the sale of
three European-based Beatrice International companies.
   The companies include Britain-based Callard & Bowser Group,
which makes and markets confectionery products; Britain-based
Beatrice Poultry, which produces and sells poultry under the
Butterball name and private labels; and Beatrice International
Bottling Group of the Netherlands and Belgium, which manufactures
soft drinks under the 7Up, Sunkist, RC Cola and Canada Dry brand
names.
   TLC said in a statement that over the past three months it has
received purchase inquiries about the businesses.
   TLC, founded by Reginald F. Lewis in 1983, completed the nearly
$1 billion leveraged buyout of Beatrice International in December.
Since then TLC has sold off a number of Beatrice's overseas
operations.
