<HEAD>Bank Of New York Extends Offer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bank of New York Co. said Monday that it
extended until Wednesday its $1 billion-plus hostile offer for
Irving Bank Corp.
   Meanwhile, both companies continued to exchange barbs, with Bank
of New York saying it would not hold any more merger talks with
Irving because the bank ``never intended to negotiate seriously.''
   Irving countered by saying it is ``disappointed'' by Bank of New
York's refusal to bargain and said its board ``remains fully
committed to obtaining the best transaction for its shareholders.''
   Bank of New York ``should return to the negotiating table if it
wants to convince Irving shareholders that its offer is the best
obtainable,'' Irving said in a statement.
   Bank of New York is offering $15 in cash and 1.575 of its common
shares for all of Irving's approximately 18 million shares
outstanding. The tender offer, which had been set to expire last
Friday, began a month ago following regulatory approval.
   As of the close of business Friday, Bank of New York said 7.68
million Irving shares had been tendered.
   Bank of New York also is running a slate of 16 nominees for
Irving's board of directors.
   Irving, however, is urging its shareholders to approve a complex
restructuring plan that includes selling a major stake to Banca
Commerciale Italiana, Italy's second-largest bank.
   Banca Commerciale Italiana, which emerged as a friendly merger
partner last week, has offered to pay $75 a share for 8.5 million
Irving shares, or a 45 percent stake in the company. Banca
Commerciale also would have the right to buy an additional 10
percent of Irving stock on the open market after the deal was
consummated.
   Bank of New York has said that Bankca Commerciale is unlikely to
receive the necessary regulatory approvals.
   Irving's proposed restructuring also includes the sale of
assets, such as its 50-story Wall Street headquarters, cost-cutting
measures, and a $10-a-share special cash dividend.
   Irving's annual shareholders' meeting is scheduled for May 6.
</TEXT>
