<2ND_LINE>BC-Nike Purchase, 1st Ld - Writethru, f0097,0190</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Nike Acquries Dress Shoe Footwear Company</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New throughout to CORRECT name of company to Cole-Haan from
Cole Haan , adds further detail, quote. No pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BEAVERTON, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nike Inc. said Monday it agreed to
acquire a privately-held New England shoe company in a deal valued
at around $95 million. The athletic shoe and apparel company said
it would buy Cole-Haan and related companies from Cole-Haan Limited
Partnership for $80 million plus $15 million in debt repayments.
   Cole-Haan, a 13-year-old company based in Yarmouth, Maine,
designs and markets classic-style footwear and accessories, ranging
from $85 boat moccasins to $500 lizard pumps. Its sales for the
year ended March 31 totaled about $62 million, Nike said.
   Cole-Haan founder George Denney and current management are
expected to remain at the company after the deal is complete.
   ``This is the execution of a strategy our board adopted over a
year ago,'' said Nike Chairman Philip H. Knight. ``It is a marriage
of the best in the athletic footwear industry with the premier
brand of dress and casual shoe in the business.''
</TEXT>
